This is a minimal Linux distribution running entirely in your browser,
powered by the v86 x86 emulator and a custom-built minimal kernel + BusyBox userspace

Getting started
---------------
You are in an interactive shell. Try these commands:

  uname -a               - show kernel version and architecture
  ls /                   - list the root filesystem
  cat /proc/cpuinfo      - show CPU information
  cat /proc/meminfo      - show memory information
  cat /proc/interrupts   - live interrupt counters
  cat /proc/net/dev      - network interface stats
  free -h                - show memory usage
  df -h                  - show filesystem disk usage
  ps                     - list running processes
  top                    - interactive process viewer
  dmesg                  - show kernel messages

Keyboard shortcuts
------------------
  Ctrl+C  - interrupt the current process (SIGINT)
  Ctrl+D  - send end-of-file / exit the shell

Notes
-----
- There is no persistent storage; changes are lost on page reload.
- Network is not available.
- The filesystem lives in an initramfs (RAM disk).

Source code: https://github.com/mauri870/tiny-linux
